348
00:21:54,219 --> 00:22:02,766
Goals are awesome and drive us to challenge ourselves and one another to achieve great things,

349
00:22:02,766 --> 00:22:06,949
but you can't gloss over those days in between deliverables.

350
00:22:06,949 --> 00:22:10,913
I don't believe that the ends justify the means.

351
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:15,217
and it's the means, those day-to-day experiences

352
00:22:15,217 --> 00:22:16,838
that really comprise the majority

353
00:22:16,838 --> 00:22:18,960
of our existence here on Earth.

354
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,342
And I think that's important to remember.

355
00:22:21,342 --> 00:22:24,025
Jim Henson really strived to create a working environment

356
00:22:24,025 --> 00:22:27,147
for his artists that was just as enjoyable to work in

357
00:22:27,147 --> 00:22:28,689
as the material that they were working on.

358
00:22:28,689 --> 00:22:31,071
And he wanted the people on his team

359
00:22:31,071 --> 00:22:35,635
to feel good day-to-day and that translates into their work.

360
00:22:36,262 --> 00:22:39,504
And I do believe that the experience you have while

361
00:22:39,504 --> 00:22:42,407
creating a work impacts the emotions felt through that work.

362
00:22:42,407 --> 00:22:45,749
I think audiences have an ability to perceive heart

363
00:22:45,749 --> 00:22:46,850
through a game.

364
00:22:46,850 --> 00:22:51,093
We often really get too focused on that next deliverable

365
00:22:51,093 --> 00:22:53,015
and not on the days we spend getting there.

366
00:22:53,015 --> 00:22:55,737
